    <p>You’re exhausted. The kind of tired that a long weekend or a vacation can’t fix. You come back, and within days (or hours), you’re right back where you started.</p>

    <p>What most leaders don’t realize is that rest is a skill. And most of us were never taught how to do it.</p>

    <p>We think rest means doing nothing—collapsing on the couch, scrolling through our phones, or trying to quiet our minds while they race through tomorrow’s meetings. But rest is something more specific, rooted in how your nervous system actually works.</p>

